children.subject: Thanks for your question! Unfortunately, no, this is an unpaid position. We are still a relatively new club, but if we are able to make a successful app, we might be able to get sponsorships down the line. :)
Thank you for this opportunity! Is this position paid?

I am glad you are excited about this opportunity! :) 

To answer your questions,

- No, you don’t need a high level of experience. We’re all students, and all we want you to have is a willingness to learn, participate, and collaborate. 
- No, you do not need to be physically present in California. All communications will be virtual, through Zoom, messenger, text message, etc.

This seems really exciting! I just wanted to ask few questions.

1. Do the positions require very high level of experience?

2. Do we have to be physically present in California? (How are the project communications going to be held?)

Thank you!
We are accepting applications on a rolling basis, and you can expect to hear from us by the end of this week or the beginning of next week!

How do we know if the google form was successfully received? (When will we hear about the results?)

Thank you :)

history.content:
Hi everyone,


Tech + Social Impact is an organization that aims to create a tight-knit community in which members can explore, have candid conversations about, and take action on ways to use technology for social good.

For Spring 2021, we are looking for students who are interested in working on a team that will create an app powered by machine learning to help people speak and communicate more effectively as well as exude more confidence. All majors and experience levels are welcome!


Apply to be a member at https://tinyurl.com/tsi2021 (apps accepted on rolling basis)
